just some dogs roamin the city

First morning @ranchlands was something out of a movie. We traveled on horseback for miles next to hundreds of bison and elk. Crossed rivers and pastures, across wide landscapes under the Sangre de Cristo Mountains. There was a unique kid-like feeling of exploring into the unknown that felt like an old John Wayne western movie.

it doesn’t get more special than sharing a space with those you love, i’ve said it once and i’ll say it again…thank you from the bottom of my boots to the tip of my hat.

so much more coming.

The second morning @ranchlands was unlike anything I’ve experienced before. We had all four seasons of weather within a 4 hour window while on horseback in the @greatsanddunesnps 

These landscapes can only tell a fraction of the feeling you get riding through the Medano Creek bed, admiring the mountains and dunes around you.

The land @ranchlands offers such a wide variety of lighting situations that is every filmmakers dream. It offers different scenarios of shadows, artistic opportunities and landscapes that are ever changing with the weather and the seasons. I cannot wait to go back and get a completely different experience from the one prior.

SCOOT INN AUSTIN TX 🤠🤠🤠 we’re grateful beyond words to have shared the night with you all, it was the pleasure of our lives and we can’t wait to see you again soon ❤️‍🔥 we offer you our fondest recap of the night. new york city, we’ll see you next 🚨

📸: @kate.liddy & @womedias
